  "text": "In case of logic networks and signal processing, we assume that the sets of values of a function f and arbitrary variable x are two finite fields [CITATION_1] . We calculate the probability p |f =b = k |f =b /k, where k |f =b is the number of assignments of values to variables for which f = b and k is the total number of assignments.",
